APE Package

Avery Shepherd

5/11/2021

The ape package (Analysis of Phylogenetics and Evolution) is used within the community of evolutionary biologists for data analysis and as a framework for the development of new analytical methods.

library(ape)

To read and load trees into R using ape, you can use the read.nexus or read.tree functions. The read.nexus function reads NEXUS formatted files while the read.tree function reads Newick formatted trees.

tree <- read.nexus("./Potential Nexus Files/T6506.nex")
tree
## 
## Phylogenetic tree with 47 tips and 45 internal nodes.
## 
## Tip labels:
##   Asteranthera_ovata_05, Sarmienta_repens, Fieldia_australis, Fieldia_australis_CHR, Mitraria_coccinea, Negria_rhabdothamnoides_Mt_Gower, ...
## 
## Rooted; no branch lengths.
